[♪ pensive music playing]

270
00:21:52,272 --> 00:21:54,941
I was so worried
because I couldn't get in touch with you.

271
00:21:57,235 --> 00:21:58,278
I see.

272
00:21:58,987 --> 00:22:00,113
I'm sorry.

273
00:22:00,489 --> 00:22:03,200
[hesitates] It was a crazy day.

274
00:22:05,243 --> 00:22:07,078
Are you feeling okay?

275
00:22:08,121 --> 00:22:09,372
Yes, thanks to you.

276
00:22:09,790 --> 00:22:10,874
[sighs]

277
00:22:12,584 --> 00:22:13,835
That's such a relief.

278
00:22:16,046 --> 00:22:19,466
But where did you go?

279
00:22:23,470 --> 00:22:24,763
Uh...

280
00:22:25,222 --> 00:22:27,891
Shouldn't you be going? You must be tired.

281
00:22:32,813 --> 00:22:33,855
Yes.

282
00:22:34,898 --> 00:22:36,274
Get home safely.

283
00:22:40,487 --> 00:22:41,905
Seeum.

284
00:22:49,329 --> 00:22:50,664
It was your music...

285
00:22:54,709 --> 00:22:57,838
that helped me survive all these years.

286
00:23:00,632 --> 00:23:02,425
My father's business went bankrupt,

287
00:23:03,176 --> 00:23:06,388
and things were so tough
I was thinking of quitting the violin.

288
00:23:08,390 --> 00:23:11,893
But by chance,
I saw your performance on TV.

289
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:21,570
The minute I saw you,
I knew I had to keep pursuing my dream.

290
00:23:23,238 --> 00:23:25,365
That's why I didn't give up.

291
00:23:27,117 --> 00:23:28,451
Your music

292
00:23:28,702 --> 00:23:30,829
gives people

293
00:23:31,329 --> 00:23:33,290
dreams, hope, and courage.

294
00:23:35,250 --> 00:23:36,960
So, I'm not going to give up.

295
00:23:37,794 --> 00:23:39,921
I'm going to try
and persuade the members to come back.

296
00:23:40,422 --> 00:23:44,092
As the concertmaster,
I'm going to keep on trying.

297
00:23:57,647 --> 00:23:58,732
Thank you.

298
00:24:00,233 --> 00:24:01,943
Knowing that's how you feel is enough.

299
00:24:05,906 --> 00:24:08,867
It's my job, so I need to take charge.

300
00:24:16,625 --> 00:24:18,084
I know you can do it.

301
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:24,883
[chuckles softly]

302
00:24:25,550 --> 00:24:26,635
[Seeum chuckling softly]

303
00:24:28,637 --> 00:24:31,139
[♪ pensive music fades]

304
00:24:33,350 --> 00:24:36,519
[♪ somber music plays]

305
00:25:03,588 --> 00:25:05,924
[phone line ringing]

306
00:25:08,885 --> 00:25:10,887
Mr. Jeon, I need to talk to you.

307
00:25:11,972 --> 00:25:14,516
[♪ somber music concludes]

308
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:17,769
- [♪ soft music playing over speakers]
- [sighs heavily]

309
00:25:19,771 --> 00:25:21,356
Let me be honest with you.

310
00:25:21,982 --> 00:25:23,692
I'm the main breadwinner,

311
00:25:24,025 --> 00:25:26,778
so I can't work
in an unstable environment.

312
00:25:27,112 --> 00:25:30,448
Everything at Hanphil
is going to go back to normal.

313
00:25:30,865 --> 00:25:34,828
Those who remain at Hanphil
will also be getting a raise.

314
00:25:35,537 --> 00:25:39,082
Really? Is that possible?

315
00:25:39,582 --> 00:25:40,583
Yes.

316
00:25:41,251 --> 00:25:42,293
[♪ dramatic music plays]

317
00:25:42,377 --> 00:25:43,837
[Sangdo over phone]
<i>Are you serious, Seeum?</i>

318
00:25:44,295 --> 00:25:47,173
<i>- How can we...</i>
- I'll take a pay cut.

319
00:25:47,424 --> 00:25:50,635
So, give the members a raise.

320
00:25:53,513 --> 00:25:56,933
Of course, salaries are important,

321
00:25:57,100 --> 00:26:00,270
but that's not enough
to persuade the members...

322
00:26:00,395 --> 00:26:01,771
Please accept my offer.

323
00:26:03,648 --> 00:26:04,733
My goodness.

324
00:26:11,573 --> 00:26:13,658
We have no intention
of changing our minds.

325
00:26:14,451 --> 00:26:16,119
Don't be so harsh.

326
00:26:16,286 --> 00:26:17,746
[♪ dramatic music continues]

327
00:26:18,788 --> 00:26:20,415
Please come back to Hanphil.

328
00:26:20,707 --> 00:26:24,044
We need you. Please reconsider.

329
00:26:25,503 --> 00:26:27,839
- [Jiae gasps]
- You don't need to bow to us.

330
00:26:28,631 --> 00:26:31,342
- It's not even your fault.
- Mm-hmm.

331
00:26:32,093 --> 00:26:33,636
The second violin is the link

332
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:35,972
between the first violin
and the other instruments.

333
00:26:36,056 --> 00:26:37,474
Its role is very important.

334
00:26:37,557 --> 00:26:40,143
Your skills and experience

335
00:26:40,226 --> 00:26:43,229
are why Hanphil
was able to create such great harmony.

336
00:26:43,521 --> 00:26:46,941
[clears throat] There's no need
to go overboard with the compliments.

337
00:26:47,233 --> 00:26:49,527
Well, we are pretty important
to the orchestra.

338
00:26:49,611 --> 00:26:50,820
[chuckles, clears throat]

339
00:26:52,947 --> 00:26:54,783
Your absence is deeply felt.

340
00:26:56,326 --> 00:26:57,535
Please come back.

341
00:27:00,288 --> 00:27:02,207
CONCERTMASTER AUDITION ROOM

342
00:27:02,832 --> 00:27:05,627
[♪ dramatic music concludes]

343
00:27:06,252 --> 00:27:07,545
Did the audition go well?

344
00:27:08,338 --> 00:27:09,464
[sighs]

345
00:27:12,092 --> 00:27:13,718
That's none of your concern.

346
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:21,601
I hear there are a lot of problems
with this orchestra.

347
00:27:22,352 --> 00:27:25,396
Half got in through connections,
so they have no talent.

348
00:27:25,897 --> 00:27:29,275
The CEO only cares about
padding his pockets by accepting bribes.

349
00:27:30,693 --> 00:27:32,612
Is being concertmaster here worth it?

350
00:27:32,737 --> 00:27:36,074
Again, where I go or what I do
is none of your business.

351
00:27:36,157 --> 00:27:38,910
Of course it concerns me.
I need you in my orchestra.

352
00:27:39,077 --> 00:27:41,121
[♪ soft music plays]

353
00:27:43,081 --> 00:27:44,624
I changed the concertmaster

354
00:27:44,707 --> 00:27:47,961
but left you
as the assistant concertmaster

355
00:27:48,419 --> 00:27:51,422
because I recognize your talent, Sujin.

356
00:27:54,676 --> 00:27:55,844
It's too late.

357
00:27:57,303 --> 00:28:00,640
I've already tried out,
and my audition was flawless.

358
00:28:03,810 --> 00:28:06,271
If you were going to a better orchestra
than Hanphil,

359
00:28:06,354 --> 00:28:07,897
I would happily let you go.

360
00:28:08,565 --> 00:28:10,233
But you don't belong here.

361
00:28:11,526 --> 00:28:12,735
Think it over.

362
00:28:20,451 --> 00:28:22,579
Sujin, come back to Hanphil.

363
00:28:25,373 --> 00:28:26,457
Please.

364
00:28:31,004 --> 00:28:32,338
[sighs heavily]

365
00:28:32,463 --> 00:28:34,090
[♪ soft music fades]

366
00:28:34,257 --> 00:28:35,341
[Hangil] <i>What brings you here?</i>

367
00:28:35,967 --> 00:28:38,511
Didn't you want to shoot a documentary?
Let's do it.

368
00:28:40,013 --> 00:28:41,973
The one Yura wanted to do
about you and Phil?

369
00:28:42,432 --> 00:28:43,975
No, a Hanphil documentary.

370
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:48,062
Why would I want to do that?

371
00:28:48,730 --> 00:28:50,148
Your image is terrible these days.

372
00:28:50,231 --> 00:28:52,525
If I say yes,
our image will also take a hit.

373
00:28:53,735 --> 00:28:55,737
That aside, do you think

374
00:28:55,820 --> 00:28:57,989
anyone will watch
a documentary on Hanphil?

375
00:28:58,948 --> 00:29:00,909
I'm positive it will get good ratings.

376
00:29:01,492 --> 00:29:03,620
[chuckles] How can you be so sure?

377
00:29:04,579 --> 00:29:06,289
Because Phil is going to host it.

378
00:29:06,623 --> 00:29:08,625
[♪ intriguing music plays]

379
00:29:08,833 --> 00:29:10,001
Your husband?

380
00:29:11,461 --> 00:29:12,921
What are you talking about?

381
00:29:13,129 --> 00:29:14,672
Didn't you turn us down?

382
00:29:16,716 --> 00:29:18,593
He's not my husband anymore.

383
00:29:20,637 --> 00:29:22,055
I'm not following...

384
00:29:22,138 --> 00:29:23,389
[cup clinking]

385
00:29:23,890 --> 00:29:26,893
What if news of our divorce broke
three days before it aired?

386
00:29:27,018 --> 00:29:30,480
Phil and Seeum are divorcing,
but they shot a documentary together?

387
00:29:30,897 --> 00:29:32,357
Wouldn't you be curious?

388
00:29:34,025 --> 00:29:35,944
So, what you're saying is...

389
00:29:36,027 --> 00:29:37,946
An exclusive on our divorce.

390
00:29:38,821 --> 00:29:42,867
Plus, a Hanphil documentary starring
the divorcing couple.

391
00:29:43,534 --> 00:29:45,954
I'll give them both to KVN.

392
00:29:49,457 --> 00:29:52,126
What do you think?
The ratings will go through the roof.

393
00:29:54,963 --> 00:29:56,047
[chuckles softly]

394
00:29:57,757 --> 00:30:00,551
If KVN turns down my offer,
I'll take it somewhere else.

395
00:30:03,054 --> 00:30:04,889
[♪ intriguing music concludes]

396
00:30:05,181 --> 00:30:06,849
[Dongsik] <i>It doesn't make sense.</i>

397
00:30:07,016 --> 00:30:08,393
[Juwon] I agree, it's strange.

398
00:30:08,768 --> 00:30:10,228
It doesn't make sense,

399
00:30:10,311 --> 00:30:12,063
but Kim Bongju's death
was ruled an accident,

400
00:30:12,146 --> 00:30:14,023
and the drug case has been dropped.

401
00:30:14,148 --> 00:30:15,483
You need to let it go.

402
00:30:15,608 --> 00:30:16,859
One distributor dies,

403
00:30:16,943 --> 00:30:19,279
and they're going to close a drug case?

404
00:30:20,822 --> 00:30:23,324
I heard the chief of police met
with Mr. Kim.

405
00:30:24,158 --> 00:30:25,868
They covered it up.

406
00:30:26,202 --> 00:30:27,787
[Juwon] That's why

407
00:30:27,954 --> 00:30:29,706
this is so dangerous.

408
00:30:29,872 --> 00:30:31,374
You've got an assemblyman,

409
00:30:31,457 --> 00:30:33,710
and the chairman of UC Financial

410
00:30:33,876 --> 00:30:35,920
putting up all these roadblocks.

411
00:30:36,212 --> 00:30:38,214
What can we possibly do?

412
00:30:39,173 --> 00:30:40,800
Find evidence.

413
00:30:41,009 --> 00:30:42,510
That will solve everything.

414
00:30:47,223 --> 00:30:50,268
[♪ pensive music plays]

415
00:30:57,692 --> 00:30:58,985
[Juwon] Did you find something?

416
00:31:07,118 --> 00:31:08,286
What is it?

417
00:31:10,496 --> 00:31:13,207
Hopefully,
this is what we've been looking for.

418
00:31:18,504 --> 00:31:21,257
[♪ pensive music continues]

419
00:31:23,968 --> 00:31:26,512
[Dongsik] <i>Kim Bongju is dead.</i>

420
00:31:27,305 --> 00:31:29,766
<i>His body was found in the Han River.</i>

421
00:31:30,600 --> 00:31:32,935
<i>Do you by any chance
know anything about this?</i>

422
00:31:53,956 --> 00:31:56,584
[Dongsik echoing] <i>Kim Bongju is dead.</i>

423
00:31:57,794 --> 00:31:59,170
[breathes shakily]

424
00:31:59,295 --> 00:32:02,006
[Dongsik] <i>His body was found
in the Han River.</i>

425
00:32:02,465 --> 00:32:06,177
<i>Do you by any chance
know anything about this?</i>

426
00:32:06,260 --> 00:32:08,429
- [♪ music turns tense]
- [breathes heavily]

427
00:32:15,895 --> 00:32:18,314
[♪ tense music fades]

428
00:32:20,566 --> 00:32:22,735
[musicians chattering]

429
00:32:25,738 --> 00:32:26,739
[exhales sharply]

430
00:32:30,701 --> 00:32:32,995
- [Yoseop chuckling]
- [in English] Good morning.

431
00:32:33,788 --> 00:32:35,123
[musician 1 in Korean] They're back.

432
00:32:35,206 --> 00:32:38,251
[♪ gentle music plays]

433
00:32:43,756 --> 00:32:44,799
[Jaeman clearing throat]

434
00:32:44,924 --> 00:32:46,008
Welcome back.

435
00:32:46,092 --> 00:32:47,427
- Hello.
- Good morning.

436
00:32:47,677 --> 00:32:48,970
- Good to have you back.
- [Jiae] Thanks.

437
00:32:49,470 --> 00:32:50,930
[Jaeman] Let's get a move on.

438
00:32:51,139 --> 00:32:53,266
[musicians chattering]

439
00:32:58,438 --> 00:33:00,398
[musician 2] They're all coming back.

440
00:33:07,905 --> 00:33:09,073
Hello.

441
00:33:09,198 --> 00:33:10,700
[musicians] Hello.

442
00:33:11,492 --> 00:33:13,911
Thank you for coming back.

443
00:33:18,708 --> 00:33:20,626
The concert is just around the corner,

444
00:33:20,710 --> 00:33:22,211
so there's no time to waste.

445
00:33:22,753 --> 00:33:25,715
As you're all aware,
we will be performing...

446
00:33:25,840 --> 00:33:27,049
[door closing]

447
00:33:30,678 --> 00:33:32,263
Sorry I'm late.

448
00:33:46,110 --> 00:33:48,404
Now everyone really is here.

449
00:33:48,488 --> 00:33:49,530
[chuckling]

450
00:33:50,281 --> 00:33:53,493
When Beethoven composed <i>Symphony No. 5,</i>

451
00:33:53,618 --> 00:33:55,036
he faced many personal struggles,

452
00:33:55,119 --> 00:33:58,164
such as a troubled love life
and a continued loss of hearing.

453
00:33:58,456 --> 00:34:01,250
In Beethoven's biography,
his assistant Anton Schindler

454
00:34:01,417 --> 00:34:03,044
quoted Beethoven as having said

455
00:34:03,169 --> 00:34:05,296
that the first movement represented

456
00:34:05,379 --> 00:34:06,964
"fate knocking on the door."

457
00:34:07,048 --> 00:34:08,674
We don't know if that's true,

458
00:34:08,758 --> 00:34:12,595
but we do know that his first movement
reflects his determination

459
00:34:12,678 --> 00:34:15,097
to fight against his approaching fate.

460
00:34:15,973 --> 00:34:18,226
You have put on many concerts
over the years.

461
00:34:18,309 --> 00:34:22,021
This time we need to show the audience

462
00:34:22,104 --> 00:34:23,231
a new side of Hanphil.

463
00:34:24,023 --> 00:34:26,692
Now then,

464
00:34:27,610 --> 00:34:29,570
shall we open the door to our fate?

465
00:34:36,160 --> 00:34:39,038
[♪ orchestra plays "Symphony No. 5"]

466
00:34:41,999 --> 00:34:43,334
[Hangil] <i>I've reworked the storyline.</i>

467
00:34:44,210 --> 00:34:47,129
It was a shame
we couldn't do the other documentary.

468
00:34:47,213 --> 00:34:48,631
So, this is what I propose.

469
00:34:48,839 --> 00:34:51,384
A documentary about Hanphil,
like Seeum wanted.

470
00:34:51,467 --> 00:34:53,177
CHA SEEUM AND HANPHIL

471
00:34:54,470 --> 00:34:56,681
What does that have to do with me?

472
00:34:57,056 --> 00:35:01,310
I would like you to conduct the interviews
in the documentary.

473
00:35:01,394 --> 00:35:02,395
Me?

474
00:35:02,728 --> 00:35:05,398
We'll prepare a list of questions for you,

475
00:35:05,773 --> 00:35:09,402
but the interview would be
far more detailed if you conducted it

476
00:35:09,485 --> 00:35:11,779
rather than the director
or the screenwriter.

477
00:35:11,946 --> 00:35:13,990
[♪ pensive music plays]

478
00:35:14,240 --> 00:35:15,283
Well...

479
00:35:17,285 --> 00:35:18,536
[Hangil] And of course...

480
00:35:19,412 --> 00:35:22,206
you also happen to be Seeum's husband.

481
00:35:28,170 --> 00:35:29,422
Tell me,

482
00:35:30,047 --> 00:35:32,800
has Hanphil already agreed to this?

483
00:35:33,092 --> 00:35:36,554
Yes, and Seeum has also agreed.

484
00:35:36,637 --> 00:35:39,390
As you know,
Hanphil is going through a tough time.

485
00:35:39,849 --> 00:35:42,727
So, they're more than happy
to be featured. [chuckling]

486
00:35:45,438 --> 00:35:46,439
I see.

487
00:35:49,817 --> 00:35:50,985
[Seeum] <i>I have one condition.</i>

488
00:35:51,527 --> 00:35:53,029
You can't tell anyone

489
00:35:53,112 --> 00:35:55,281
that I'm planning to announce my divorce.

490
00:35:55,948 --> 00:35:58,618
- That goes without saying.
- That includes Jeongjae.

491
00:36:00,077 --> 00:36:01,120
Huh?

492
00:36:01,495 --> 00:36:02,622
And Phil.

493
00:36:03,873 --> 00:36:04,874
Right.

494
00:36:14,383 --> 00:36:17,219
Is there anything that concerns you?

495
00:36:20,806 --> 00:36:22,058
I'll do it.

496
00:36:25,436 --> 00:36:27,772
This should be fun, for many reasons.

497
00:36:28,481 --> 00:36:29,565
[chuckles softly]

498
00:36:30,399 --> 00:36:31,400
[door opening]

499
00:36:31,484 --> 00:36:33,277
[Yura sighing, yelling] Are you crazy?

500
00:36:33,361 --> 00:36:35,571
What the hell? I'm in a meeting right now.

501
00:36:37,073 --> 00:36:38,324
- [sighs]
- [♪ pensive music fades]

502
00:36:38,407 --> 00:36:40,660
- There's a face I don't want to see.
- [Hangil] Get out.

503
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:42,286
Hello, Ms. Go.

504
00:36:43,037 --> 00:36:44,163
[Yura sighs]

505
00:36:46,499 --> 00:36:49,502
Perfect timing.
That's what I came to see you about.

506
00:36:50,127 --> 00:36:51,295
What?

507
00:36:51,671 --> 00:36:54,048
Why are you leaving me out
of the documentary?

508
00:36:54,965 --> 00:36:57,093
It was my idea.
Why are you leaving me out?

509
00:36:57,176 --> 00:36:59,845
This is something completely different.
[clicking tongue]

510
00:37:00,012 --> 00:37:01,514
- I want to do it.
- [Hangil] No.

511
00:37:02,390 --> 00:37:04,558
- Why not?
- Because I said so.

512
00:37:04,684 --> 00:37:06,644
- Get out. I'm sorry.
- [cries out] Why?

513
00:37:06,769 --> 00:37:08,145
- [Hangil] Let's talk outside.
- [Yura] No.

514
00:37:08,270 --> 00:37:09,730
[Hangil] Come with me. Sorry.

515
00:37:09,814 --> 00:37:13,609
[Yura and Hangil bickering]

516
00:37:13,734 --> 00:37:15,653
- [Hangil] What are you doing?
- [Yura] What?

517
00:37:29,041 --> 00:37:30,084
[chuckles softly]

518
00:37:34,130 --> 00:37:36,882
[chuckles] What a great opportunity.

519
00:37:37,007 --> 00:37:39,009
Where there's a will, there's a way.

520
00:37:39,093 --> 00:37:41,220
How did we get so lucky? [chuckles]

521
00:37:41,470 --> 00:37:43,723
I know, it's perfect timing.

522
00:37:43,889 --> 00:37:45,391
This time, even Seeum is on board.

523
00:37:45,850 --> 00:37:48,477
Things are slowly
starting to fall into place.

524
00:37:48,769 --> 00:37:51,397
Is it true that Professor Kim is the host?

525
00:37:52,022 --> 00:37:54,024
Does Ms. Cha know that?

526
00:37:54,608 --> 00:37:56,318
That Professor Kim is the host?

527
00:37:57,194 --> 00:37:59,405
Of course she knows, she saw the proposal.

528
00:37:59,488 --> 00:38:01,574
