629
00:45:06,999 --> 00:45:09,418
- It's a waste of money.
- [Jiae grunting disapprovingly]

630
00:45:13,088 --> 00:45:15,883
That's because you're both
naturally beautiful.

631
00:45:16,008 --> 00:45:17,551
- [laughing]
- [door opening]

632
00:45:17,718 --> 00:45:19,178
- [Ajin] Hello.
- [Yoseop] Hi.

633
00:45:19,344 --> 00:45:20,470
Hello.

634
00:45:20,971 --> 00:45:22,890
[gasps] Ajin,

635
00:45:23,140 --> 00:45:25,559
you look like you've put on a few pounds.

636
00:45:25,934 --> 00:45:26,977
I...

637
00:45:27,561 --> 00:45:29,605
I've gained some weight.

638
00:45:29,813 --> 00:45:31,899
Come to think of it,
you changed your style.

639
00:45:32,107 --> 00:45:33,150
You only wore heels,

640
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:34,735
but now you only wear flats.

641
00:45:35,402 --> 00:45:37,571
[Baha] Oh! Professor Kim! [chuckling]

642
00:45:38,322 --> 00:45:39,615
[musicians] Hello.

643
00:45:39,781 --> 00:45:40,949
[Phil] Hello.

644
00:45:42,409 --> 00:45:44,077
[♪ tense music plays]

645
00:45:44,203 --> 00:45:46,413
It's been a long time, Professor.

646
00:45:47,998 --> 00:45:49,082
Yes, it has.

647
00:45:53,378 --> 00:45:56,006
Uh, is everyone doing well?

648
00:45:56,089 --> 00:45:57,925
- [group] Yes.
- [Baha] Of course. [laughs]

649
00:45:58,342 --> 00:46:00,344
[Phil] Let's have a good shoot today.

650
00:46:00,677 --> 00:46:02,471
[musicians] We're looking forward to it.

651
00:46:03,347 --> 00:46:04,473
CHA SEEUM AND HANPHIL

652
00:46:04,598 --> 00:46:06,642
QUESTIONS FOR CHA SEEUM

653
00:46:06,725 --> 00:46:08,310
- [♪ tense music fades]
- [knocking on door]

654
00:46:09,353 --> 00:46:10,771
[Seeum] Yes?

655
00:46:13,690 --> 00:46:14,733
Hi.

656
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:16,443
[director] Hello.

657
00:46:16,526 --> 00:46:17,861
Hello.

658
00:46:18,278 --> 00:46:19,279
Let's do this.

659
00:46:21,615 --> 00:46:23,617
Should we do the interview over here?

660
00:46:24,368 --> 00:46:25,744
That sounds good.

661
00:46:26,787 --> 00:46:27,871
Are you okay...

662
00:46:29,373 --> 00:46:30,540
today?

663
00:46:34,002 --> 00:46:35,545
I'm ready to go.

664
00:46:39,549 --> 00:46:43,387
[director] For today's interview,
we'll mainly follow the script

665
00:46:43,470 --> 00:46:44,763
we provided to you.

666
00:46:45,889 --> 00:46:47,307
[Phil] Recently,

667
00:46:47,683 --> 00:46:51,270
you opened up about Remington's disease.

668
00:46:52,980 --> 00:46:54,022
Yes.

669
00:46:55,065 --> 00:46:58,360
I spoke about the possibility
of getting Remington's disease.

670
00:46:58,485 --> 00:47:00,654
Yes, "the possibility."

671
00:47:01,947 --> 00:47:04,908
And should the symptoms start to appear,

672
00:47:05,617 --> 00:47:09,037
you would voluntarily
step down from your position.

673
00:47:11,665 --> 00:47:13,083
Yes, that's correct.

674
00:47:16,837 --> 00:47:18,088
Tell us,

675
00:47:18,922 --> 00:47:23,051
what does standing on the podium
mean to you?

676
00:47:23,302 --> 00:47:25,220
- [♪ dramatic music plays]
- [sighs]

677
00:47:25,345 --> 00:47:26,596
It's like a battlefield.

678
00:47:27,264 --> 00:47:29,308
- [Phil] A battlefield?
- [Seeum] Yes.

679
00:47:31,059 --> 00:47:35,772
The members are in front of me,
and the audience is behind me.

680
00:47:36,064 --> 00:47:39,860
The conductor
is the center of everyone's attention.

681
00:47:40,527 --> 00:47:43,905
In some ways, I'm standing
on the opposite side of everyone.

682
00:47:43,989 --> 00:47:48,744
So, the stage is like a battlefield
with enemies on all sides.

683
00:47:49,953 --> 00:47:52,039
If it's that much pressure,

684
00:47:52,539 --> 00:47:55,459
do you ever think about stepping down
before your time?

685
00:47:59,296 --> 00:48:02,841
I quite enjoy the adrenaline rush.

686
00:48:03,842 --> 00:48:04,926
[chuckles softly]

687
00:48:05,385 --> 00:48:06,470
I see.

688
00:48:12,100 --> 00:48:15,187
[♪ orchestra playing dramatic movement
of "Symphony No. 5"]

689
00:48:23,070 --> 00:48:24,780
[inaudible]

690
00:48:40,420 --> 00:48:45,634
[♪ dramatic melodic motive plays]

691
00:48:58,522 --> 00:49:00,399
[♪ music concludes]

692
00:49:01,983 --> 00:49:03,235
Okay.

693
00:49:08,532 --> 00:49:11,201
Our current share price is 18,500 won,

694
00:49:11,284 --> 00:49:13,245
- our revenue is 29 billion won...
- [cell phone buzzing]

695
00:49:13,370 --> 00:49:14,955
...and operating profit is 1.4 billion.

696
00:49:15,122 --> 00:49:18,625
Revenue has increased 22%
compared to Q1 of last year.

697
00:49:18,708 --> 00:49:20,669
So, revenue for the latter half...

698
00:49:20,752 --> 00:49:22,587
- [Taeho] <i>They're shooting now.</i>
- [cell phone buzzing]

699
00:49:22,671 --> 00:49:24,673
[presenter] The dramas we introduced
early this year

700
00:49:24,756 --> 00:49:27,551
were very popular in Taiwan, Thailand,
and Indonesia.

701
00:49:27,843 --> 00:49:30,637
And the feedback indicates
they should do well globally.

702
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:32,222
Additionally, our sales...

703
00:49:36,852 --> 00:49:37,853
What do you want?

704
00:49:39,187 --> 00:49:40,730
What kind of greeting is that?

705
00:49:42,691 --> 00:49:44,693
[Jeongjae] If it's not important, go home.
I'm tired.

706
00:49:45,986 --> 00:49:47,028
[sighs]

707
00:49:53,118 --> 00:49:54,828
It's important.

708
00:49:56,705 --> 00:49:59,541
I heard you sold your shares
because of Hanphil.

709
00:49:59,875 --> 00:50:01,251
- What's it to you?
- [Yura scoffing]

710
00:50:01,376 --> 00:50:03,837
It's been 20 years.
Why is she still so important?

711
00:50:04,087 --> 00:50:06,339
Since when have you been such a romantic?

712
00:50:06,965 --> 00:50:07,966
It doesn't suit you.

713
00:50:08,049 --> 00:50:10,469
You seem to have forgotten we're divorced.

714
00:50:10,552 --> 00:50:11,678
You need to stop this.

715
00:50:12,971 --> 00:50:16,516
It's not like we got married
because we were madly in love.

716
00:50:16,641 --> 00:50:18,310
[mouse scrolling, clicking]

717
00:50:21,062 --> 00:50:23,273
Did you ever really...

718
00:50:23,356 --> 00:50:24,941
Why are you acting like this?

719
00:50:25,025 --> 00:50:26,359
Did we marry for love?

720
00:50:27,068 --> 00:50:28,528
What did you expect from me?

721
00:50:28,904 --> 00:50:29,988
Cha Seeum.

722
00:50:30,655 --> 00:50:33,116
She's using you.

723
00:50:33,366 --> 00:50:36,161
She's shooting a documentary
with Phil today.

724
00:50:36,244 --> 00:50:38,955
- [♪ tense music plays]
- So, stop letting her play you for a fool.

725
00:50:39,080 --> 00:50:40,081
That's enough.

726
00:50:49,341 --> 00:50:51,927
I've had enough of your little games.

727
00:50:56,681 --> 00:50:57,682
[scoffs softly]

728
00:51:00,936 --> 00:51:03,230
- [typing]
- [Phil] <i>I think we're done here.</i>

729
00:51:03,480 --> 00:51:05,440
- [♪ tense music fades]
- I have one last question.

730
00:51:05,524 --> 00:51:07,859
You're Hanphil's youngest concertmaster.

731
00:51:07,943 --> 00:51:10,695
What is your goal?

732
00:51:11,279 --> 00:51:13,698
I want to continue working with Seeum.

733
00:51:14,491 --> 00:51:15,659
Can you elaborate?

734
00:51:15,909 --> 00:51:17,369
[Luna] Hmm.

735
00:51:17,827 --> 00:51:19,829
I want to work with Seeum

736
00:51:19,996 --> 00:51:23,833
to turn Hanphil into a great orchestra.

737
00:51:24,459 --> 00:51:26,002
That's my goal.

738
00:51:26,294 --> 00:51:27,587
Ah, I see.

739
00:51:28,588 --> 00:51:32,133
Uh, I hope you achieve your goal.

740
00:51:32,592 --> 00:51:33,802
Thank you.

741
00:51:34,761 --> 00:51:36,930
Cut. Good job.

742
00:51:37,138 --> 00:51:39,057
- Nice work.
- [Luna and Phil] Thank you.

743
00:51:39,933 --> 00:51:42,227
- [Luna] Thank you.
- Nice job.

744
00:51:45,897 --> 00:51:48,775
Did you conduct the interview
with Seeum as well?

745
00:51:49,818 --> 00:51:51,611
Of course.

746
00:51:51,820 --> 00:51:54,072
- [♪ intriguing music plays]
- Oh. [chuckles]

747
00:51:54,990 --> 00:51:56,449
You're really something else.

748
00:51:58,076 --> 00:51:59,119
How so?

749
00:52:02,122 --> 00:52:04,416
I just mean you must be
really busy. [chuckles]

750
00:52:06,835 --> 00:52:09,379
[chuckles] Good job.

751
00:52:11,089 --> 00:52:12,257
Thanks, everyone.

752
00:52:19,180 --> 00:52:21,516
[♪ intriguing music continues]

753
00:52:24,060 --> 00:52:25,687
- Thank you.
- [production crew responds]

754
00:52:25,854 --> 00:52:27,355
[director] Well done.

755
00:52:27,439 --> 00:52:28,648
Help her with her mic.

756
00:52:31,401 --> 00:52:32,402
Thank you.

757
00:52:32,861 --> 00:52:33,862
Thank you.

758
00:52:33,945 --> 00:52:35,947
- [director] You did a great job.
- [Luna] I didn't do much.

759
00:52:36,031 --> 00:52:37,240
[chuckling] I didn't do anything.

760
00:52:37,616 --> 00:52:39,951
[♪ intriguing music continues]

761
00:52:46,916 --> 00:52:49,711
{\an8}TEST

