00:54:49,873 --> 00:54:51,291
Where are you going?

789
00:54:54,377 --> 00:54:55,420
SEOUL FAMILY COURT

790
00:54:55,503 --> 00:54:56,963
[Phil] I signed them.

791
00:54:57,046 --> 00:54:58,256
I won't contest the divorce.

792
00:55:01,926 --> 00:55:02,927
Honey.

793
00:55:06,389 --> 00:55:08,016
My feet are killing me.

794
00:55:11,644 --> 00:55:13,188
Bring me my shoes.

795
00:55:14,481 --> 00:55:15,565
Ooh!

796
00:55:18,943 --> 00:55:20,987
Sure, okay.

797
00:55:22,030 --> 00:55:25,325
[sighs] Wait here a minute.

798
00:55:26,910 --> 00:55:29,746
[♪ music turns suspenseful]

799
00:55:46,971 --> 00:55:49,474
[Phil] <i>I was so worried
because you disappeared.</i>

800
00:55:49,974 --> 00:55:52,101
It looked like you had a lot to drink.

801
00:55:55,688 --> 00:55:59,317
Wait, have the symptoms started?

802
00:56:01,069 --> 00:56:04,864
If you don't even remember seeing me,

803
00:56:06,324 --> 00:56:08,409
it can't just be because of the alcohol.

804
00:56:11,496 --> 00:56:13,581
I'm sure you remember this.

805
00:56:14,249 --> 00:56:15,750
If the symptoms start,

806
00:56:16,084 --> 00:56:18,962
you'll step down from the podium.

807
00:56:19,254 --> 00:56:21,381
[♪ music turns tense]

808
00:56:24,300 --> 00:56:25,468
Does that mean...

809
00:56:27,095 --> 00:56:29,055
this will be your final concert?

810
00:56:31,349 --> 00:56:32,517
[chuckling]

811
00:56:38,523 --> 00:56:40,692
I should have at least
brought some flowers.

812
00:56:47,782 --> 00:56:49,993
[♪ tense music concludes]

813
00:56:57,166 --> 00:56:59,752
The National Forensic Service called.
It's his.

814
00:57:00,169 --> 00:57:03,006
The fingerprints on the jackknife
belong to Kim Bongju.

815
00:57:03,506 --> 00:57:04,591
What about the blood?

816
00:57:05,884 --> 00:57:09,178
It doesn't belong to him.
It belongs to a female with type B blood.

817
00:57:24,402 --> 00:57:28,114
[♪ soft suspenseful music plays]

818
00:57:52,764 --> 00:57:54,933
[audience applauding]

819
00:58:24,045 --> 00:58:26,589
[♪ orchestra playing tuning notes]

820
00:58:32,178 --> 00:58:35,181
[♪ somber choral music playing]

821
00:58:59,247 --> 00:59:00,456
Seeum.

822
00:59:15,013 --> 00:59:17,140
[audience applauding]

823
00:59:23,646 --> 00:59:25,273
[echoing rumbling]

824
00:59:25,398 --> 00:59:26,607
[Phil] <i>Does that mean...</i>

825
00:59:28,192 --> 00:59:29,986
<i>this will be your final concert?</i>

826
00:59:48,546 --> 00:59:50,131
[applause fades]

827
00:59:59,307 --> 01:00:02,060
[♪ somber choral music concludes]

828
01:00:06,647 --> 01:00:08,649
[♪ orchestra plays "Symphony No. 5"]

829
01:00:09,358 --> 01:00:11,944
[♪ dramatic music playing]

830
01:00:24,415 --> 01:00:27,585
[♪ dramatic melodic motive plays]

831
01:00:48,898 --> 01:00:53,569
[♪ music turns gentle]

832
01:00:59,617 --> 01:01:01,077
[echoing] Why did you kill me?

833
01:01:08,084 --> 01:01:11,087
[♪ music turns thrilling]

834
01:01:13,422 --> 01:01:14,674
[echoing] Seeum...

835
01:01:15,716 --> 01:01:16,759
Monster.

836
01:01:26,853 --> 01:01:28,521
[♪ music concludes]

837
01:01:30,064 --> 01:01:32,859
[echoing ringing]

838
01:01:34,318 --> 01:01:35,319
- [thud]
- [gasps]

839
01:01:35,403 --> 01:01:36,612
Seeum!

840
01:01:36,737 --> 01:01:38,489
[♪ ominous music plays]

841
01:01:38,614 --> 01:01:39,699
Se...

842
01:01:41,742 --> 01:01:45,121
- [echoing rumbling]
- [musicians gasping, murmuring]

843
01:01:45,913 --> 01:01:47,206
[♪ melancholic pop song plays]

844
01:01:47,290 --> 01:01:50,001
[Seeum] <i>This is how fate
comes knocking on your door.</i>

845
01:01:51,961 --> 01:01:53,254
<i>Inevitably.</i>

846
01:01:55,965 --> 01:01:57,091
<i>With cruelty.</i>

847
01:01:59,802 --> 01:02:02,555
<i>♪ Sometimes, it's hard ♪</i>

848
01:02:02,930 --> 01:02:06,767
<i>♪ And it feels dark ♪</i>

849
01:02:06,976 --> 01:02:13,900
<i>♪ The fate that has blocked me
is watching ♪</i>

850
01:02:14,734 --> 01:02:21,282
<i>♪ Like a shadow ♪</i>

851
01:02:26,454 --> 01:02:29,749
<i>♪ Cold glances... ♪</i>

852
01:02:30,875 --> 01:02:33,336
MAESTRA: STRINGS OF TRUTH

853
01:02:33,669 --> 01:02:36,047
{\an8}What if you forget again? Like that night.

854
01:02:36,172 --> 01:02:38,174
{\an8}[Assistant Hwang] <i>Are you leaving Hanphil?</i>

855
01:02:38,299 --> 01:02:39,967
{\an8}I'm leaving. I'm sorry.

856
01:02:40,176 --> 01:02:41,344
{\an8}[Luna] <i>You can't do this.</i>

857
01:02:41,427 --> 01:02:43,054
{\an8}You can't throw it all away!

858
01:02:43,179 --> 01:02:45,181
{\an8}I can't face losing everything.

859
01:02:45,306 --> 01:02:47,391
{\an8}[Jeongjae] <i>Open this door right now.
A patient is missing.</i>

860
01:02:47,642 --> 01:02:49,602
{\an8}[Phil] <i>She shouldn't be alone.</i>

861
01:02:49,685 --> 01:02:50,811
{\an8}[Luna] <i>You said, "together."</i>

862
01:02:51,145 --> 01:02:53,940
{\an8}[Jeongjae] <i>What can I do
to help Seeum get better?</i>

863
01:02:54,440 --> 01:02:55,733
{\an8}Seeum!

864
01:02:55,816 --> 01:02:57,652
{\an8}<i>Can't you see how hard I'm trying?</i>

865
01:02:57,902 --> 01:02:59,070
{\an8}I want to live too.

866
01:02:59,153 --> 01:03:00,738
<i>But there's no other way.</i>

867
01:03:04,951 --> 01:03:06,827
Translated by Erica Lee
